'''Cannabis in Kuwait''' is illegal. 

==Enforcement==
Use and possession for personal use of cannabis can result in two years in jail plus fines.<ref>{{citation|title=Marijuana and the law in Kuwait|newspaper=[[Kuwait Times]]|author=Fajer Ahmed|date=April 3, 2016|url=http://news.kuwaittimes.net/website/marijuana-law-kuwait/}}</ref> Punishment for drug-related crimes can be severe,<ref>{{citation|publisher=U.S. Department of State Bureau of Consular Affairs|title=Travel to Kuwait|url=https://travel.state.gov/content/travel/en/international-travel/International-Travel-Country-Information-Pages/Kuwait.html|accessdate=2018-01-12}}</ref> up to and including the death penalty.<ref>{{citation|newspaper=Kuwait Times|author=Indian Embassy in Kuwait|title=Embassy releases advisory regarding drugs for Indian community in Kuwait|date=July 26, 2015|url=http://news.kuwaittimes.net/website/embassy-releases-advisory-regarding-drugs-for-indian-community-in-kuwait/}}</ref>

==International smuggling==
Cannabis and other drugs are transshipped from Afghanistan through Iran, to Kuwait, then to Europe.<ref name="Ulrichsen 2014 p. 44">{{cite book | last=Ulrichsen | first=K.C. | title=Insecure Gulf: The End of Certainty and the Transition to the Post-oil Era | publisher=Oxford University Press | year=2014 | isbn=978-0-19-025744-6 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jpr4BQAAQBAJ&pg=PT44 | access-date=2018-01-13 | page=44}}</ref>

