'''Nael Jamil al-Ajlouni''' (died 20 February 2015) was a [[Jordan]]ian doctor and politician, serving as [[Health minister|Health Minister]] in 1998.
Al-Ajlouni was director of the [[Jordanian Royal Medical Services]] with the rank of [[major general]] between 26 May 1988 and 15 August 1989.<ref>{{cite web |author= |url=http://www.jrms.gov.jo/Default.aspx?tabid=697&language=en-US |title=The JRMS General Directors Honorary Board |publisher=Jordanian Royal Medical Services |accessdate=14 March 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402092028/http://www.jrms.gov.jo/Default.aspx?tabid=697&language=en-US |archivedate=2 April 2015 |df= }}</ref> He became Health Minister of Jordan in 1998.<ref name=jordantimes>{{cite web|author= |url=http://jordantimes.com/former-health-minister-nael-ajlouni-dies |title=Former health minister Nael Ajlouni dies |publisher=The Jordan Times |date=21 February 2015 |accessdate=14 March 2015}}</ref> After his term as Minister he led a national committee looking into the possibilities of universal health care coverage.<ref name="MaedaHarrit2012">{{cite book|author1=Akiko Maeda|author2=Margareta Norris Harrit|author3=Shunsuke Mabuchi |author4=Banafsheh Siadat |author5=Somil Nagpal|title=Creating Evidence for Better Health Financing Decisions: A Strategic Guide for the Institutionalization of National Health Accounts|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=TR312rn22PgC&pg=PA189|date=18 June 2012|publisher=World Bank Publications|isbn=978-0-8213-9470-0|pages=189–}}</ref>
In January 2010 al-Ajlouni became member of the board of trustees of the [[Jordanian National Centre for Human Rights]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.nchr.org.jo/english/DataCenter/News/tabid/96/cmd445/arch/archDt445/012010/~/Default.aspx?tabid=96&mid=445&newsid445=1 |title=A Royal Decree issued to appoint new members to the Board of the Trustees of the National Center for Human Rights |publisher=The National Centre for Human Rights |accessdate=14 March 2015}}</ref> He died on 20 February 2015.<ref name=jordantimes/>
